chunks.html_content: You must tell DVLA if you experience anxiety and it affects your ability to drive safely.
chunks.plain_content:
Anxiety and driving
You must tell DVLA if you experience anxiety and it affects your ability to drive safely.

chunks.html_content: You can be fined up to £1,000 if you don’t tell DVLA about a medical condition that affects your driving. You may be prosecuted if you’re involved in an accident as a result.
chunks.plain_content:
Anxiety and driving
You can be fined up to £1,000 if you don’t tell DVLA about a medical condition that affects your driving. You may be prosecuted if you’re involved in an accident as a result.

chunks.html_content:
Ask your doctor if you’re not sure if your anxiety will affect your driving.

You must tell DVLA if your condition will affect your driving. Fill in the M1 questionnaire and send it to DVLA - the address is on the form.
